<TITLE> Hunt on for militancy funders </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 16 (bdnews24.com)The government is looking into allegations that certain NGOs and banksIslami Bank, for instanceare channelling funds to militants, the state minister for law said on Thursday. "If the allegations are proved, action will be taken against these organisations," Kamrul Islam told reporters at the secretariat. He also defended the so-called "delay" in setting up a war crimes investigation agency, and disagreed with the suggestion that it was due to stagnation in the government. "It's taking time because we want to ensure transparency," he said. "This is not stagnation." The law minister, Shafiq Ahmed, had said on Apr 9 that the agency would be set up the following week, and prosecutors appointed and tribunal formed within two weeks. "We'll name the investigators and prosecutors next week," Kamrul Islam said. Replying to questions, the state minister said: "The authorities will also serve the notice on Khaleda Zia next week to vacate the 9-bigha cantonment house." He however ruled out any move to evict the BNP from its central office in Naya Paltan. "No such step will be taken in future.
